{% elif language == "typescript" or language == "javascript" %}
- Use project's configured linter (eslint, biome, etc.)
- Run tests with the configured test runner (jest, vitest, etc.)
- Check `tsconfig.json` for compiler settings
- Prefer strict TypeScript patterns
{% elif language == "go" %}
- Use `go vet` and `golint` for code quality
- Run tests with `go test ./...`
- Follow Go conventions (exported names, error handling patterns)
{% elif language == "rust" %}
- Use `cargo clippy` for linting
- Run tests with `cargo test`
- Follow Rust idioms (Result types, ownership patterns)
{% else %}
- Check for project-specific linter and test configurations
- Follow the language's community conventions
{% endif %}

